snippet: The Dutch electorate will go to the polls on Wednesday with economic stagnation and euro skepticism on its mind, in a vote that may foreshadow next year’s elections in Germany.
abstract: Dutch voters are once again confronting issues related to the euro and economic stagnation, as well as their relationship to struggling Greece, as they head to the polls; tide of opinions in the Netherlands, often an early indicator of sentiments throughout the rest of Europe, is being watched closely ahead of the more important German political campaign to come in 2013.
lead_paragraph: The Dutch electorate will go to the polls on Wednesday with economic stagnation and euro skepticism on its mind, in a vote that may foreshadow next year’s elections in Germany.

headline.main: Dutch Voters May Point Way for Rest of Europe
headline.print_headline: Dutch Voters May Point Way for Rest of Europe
